  "code_change": {
    "files": [
      "hipengine/runtime/qwen35_paro_runner.py",
      "tests/test_qwen35_resident_batch_layout.py"
    ],
    "summary": "Rowchunked full-attention decode now forces row-aware batch_gemv O projection for every multi-row chunk, including the leading chunk, instead of only nonzero/tail chunks.",
    "unit_test": "pytest -q tests/test_qwen35_resident_batch_layout.py::test_qwen35_resident_run_layers_batch_decode_chunks_native_full_attention -q"
  },
  "conclusion": "The stale compact derived-row rowchunk2 failure was not prompt content, slot compaction, or grouped MoE. Compact rows4..7 rowchunk1 was green, and compact rows4..7 rowchunk2 became green before the patch when the full-attention O projection was explicitly forced to batch_gemv. The patch makes that output repair the default rowchunked path for every multi-row chunk, including the leading chunk; post-patch compact c3 rows4..6 and compact c4 rows4..7 rowchunk2 are green ([137]*3 and [137]*4), while original c4/c8 remain green ([137]*4 and [137]*8). This eliminates the leading-rowchunk native O-projection correctness blocker for the rowchunk diagnostic path. It does not make c4/c8 retained-ready because rowchunked full attention still reports native_caware_decode=false and full-native no-rowchunk grouping remains blocked. No throughput claim is made.",
